## Overview
Integrate the natural language cron parser with Pryx's scheduler service. The parser should seamlessly convert human-readable expressions into cron jobs.

## Integration Points

### 1. API Integration

#### Add Job Endpoint
```typescript
// POST /api/cron/jobs
interface AddJobRequest {
  name: string;
  schedule: string | CronSchedule;  // Accept natural language or structured
  payload: Payload;
  sessionTarget: "main" | "isolated";
  tz?: string;  // Timezone for natural language parsing
}

// Example requests
{
  "name": "Morning Briefing",
  "schedule": "every day at 9am",  // Natural language
  "tz": "America/New_York",        // Optional timezone
  "payload": {
    "kind": "agentTurn",
    "message": "Generate morning briefing"
  },
  "sessionTarget": "isolated"
}

{
  "name": "Health Check",
  "schedule": "every 5 minutes",   // Natural language
  "payload": {
    "kind": "systemEvent",
    "text": "Run health check"
  },
  "sessionTarget": "main"
}
```

#### Response Handling
```typescript
interface AddJobResponse {
  success: boolean;
  job?: CronJob;
  error?: {
    code: string;
    message: string;
    suggestion?: string;
  };
}

// Success
{
  "success": true,
  "job": {
    "id": "job-123",
    "name": "Morning Briefing",
    "schedule": { kind: "cron", expr: "0 9 * * *", tz: "America/New_York" },
    "nextRun": "2026-01-30T14:00:00Z"
  }
}

// Error
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "UNSUPPORTED_PATTERN",
    "message": "'every payday' is not supported",
    "suggestion": "Try: 'every 2 weeks on Friday at 9am'"
  }
}
```

### 2. CLI Integration

#### Cron Add Command
```bash
# Natural language schedule
pryx cron add \
  --name "Morning Briefing" \
  --schedule "every day at 9am" \
  --tz "America/New_York" \
  --message "Generate morning briefing"

# One-shot reminder
pryx cron add \
  --name "Meeting Reminder" \
  --schedule "in 30 minutes" \
  --session main \
  --system-event "Meeting starts in 5 minutes"

# With validation error
pryx cron add \
  --name "Payday Task" \
  --schedule "every payday"
# Error: 'every payday' is not supported. Try: 'every 2 weeks on Friday at 9am'
```

### 3. Service Integration

#### Cron Service Interface
```typescript
interface CronService {
  addJob(request: AddJobRequest): Promise<AddJobResponse>;
  parseSchedule(input: string, tz?: string): ParseResult;
}

class CronServiceImpl implements CronService {
  private parser: NaturalLanguageCronParser;
  private scheduler: Scheduler;

  async addJob(request: AddJobRequest): Promise<AddJobResponse> {
    // Parse natural language if string
    let schedule: CronSchedule;
    if (typeof request.schedule === "string") {
      const parseResult = this.parser.parse(request.schedule, request.tz);
      if (!parseResult.success) {
        return { success: false, error: parseResult.error };
      }
      schedule = parseResult.schedule;
    } else {
      schedule = request.schedule;
    }

    // Create job with parsed schedule
    const job = await this.scheduler.createJob({
      name: request.name,
      schedule,
      payload: request.payload,
      sessionTarget: request.sessionTarget
    });

    return { success: true, job };
  }

  parseSchedule(input: string, tz?: string): ParseResult {
    return this.parser.parse(input, tz);
  }
}
```

### 4. Agent Tool Integration

#### Cron Tool Update
```typescript
// In agent tools, support natural language
const CronToolSchema = Type.Object({
  action: stringEnum(CRON_ACTIONS),
  // ... other fields
  schedule: Type.Union([
    Type.String({ description: "Natural language schedule (e.g., 'every day at 9am')" }),
    Type.Object({}) // Structured schedule object
  ]),
  tz: Type.Optional(Type.String({ description: "Timezone (e.g., 'America/New_York')" }))
});

// Tool description update
const description = `Manage Gateway cron jobs...

SCHEDULE FORMAT:
You can use natural language for schedules:
- "every 5 minutes" - Every 5 minutes
- "every day at 9am" - Daily at 9:00 AM
- "every weekday at 8pm" - Monday-Friday at 8:00 PM
- "every Monday" - Every Monday
- "in 30 minutes" - One-shot in 30 minutes
- "tomorrow at 2pm" - One-shot tomorrow at 2:00 PM

For unsupported patterns, the system will suggest alternatives.
`;
```

### 5. Validation Pipeline

```
User Input
    ↓
Pre-validation (syntax check)
    ↓
Natural Language Parser
    ↓
┌─────────────┴─────────────┐
│                           │
Success                 Failure
│                           │
Structured            Error Handler
Schedule                  │
│                      Return
│                      Error + Suggestion
│
Post-validation (schedule validity)
    ↓
Scheduler Registration
    ↓
Job Created
```

### 6. Timezone Handling

```typescript
interface ParseOptions {
  tz?: string;  // IANA timezone identifier
  referenceTime?: number;  // Base time for relative expressions (default: now)
}

// Examples
parse("every day at 9am", { tz: "America/New_York" });
// Returns: { kind: "cron", expr: "0 9 * * *", tz: "America/New_York" }

parse("tomorrow at noon", { tz: "Asia/Tokyo" });
// Returns: { kind: "at", atMs: <tomorrow noon in Tokyo> }
```

